Functions

Background

  • Background(): Context
    • Defined in index.ts:89

    Background returns a empty Context. It is never canceled, has no values, and has no deadline. It is typically used by the main function, initialization, and tests, and as the top-level Context for incoming requests.

    Returns Context

TODO

  • TODO(): Context
    • Defined in index.ts:100

    TODO returns a empty Context. Code should use context.TODO when it's unclear which Context to use or it is not yet available (because the surrounding function has not yet been extended to accept a Context parameter). TODO is recognized by static analysis tools that determine whether Contexts are propagated correctly in a program.

    Returns Context

WithCancel

  • WithCancel(ctx: Context): [Context, function]
    • Defined in index.ts:160

    WithCancel returns a copy of parent with a new Done promise. The returned context's Done promise is resolved when the returned cancel function is called or when the parent context's Done promsie is resolved, whichever happens first.

    Canceling this context releases resources associated with it, so code should call cancel as soon as the operations running in this Context complete.

    Parameters

    • ctx: Context

      The parent promise

    Returns [Context, function]

WithDeadline

  • WithDeadline(ctx: Context, deadline: Date): [Context, function]
    • Defined in index.ts:228

    WithDeadline returns a copy of the parent context with the deadline adjusted to be no later than deadline. If the parent's deadline is already earlier than deadline, WithDeadline(parent, deadline) is semantically equivalent to parent. The returned context's Done promise is resolved when the deadline expires, when the returned cancel function is called, or when the parent context's Done promise is resolved, whichever happens first.

    Canceling this context releases resources associated with it, so code should call cancel as soon as the operations running in this Context complete.

    Parameters

    • ctx: Context

      The parent context

    • deadline: Date

      The date when the deadline will be exceeded

    Returns [Context, function]

WithTimeout

  • WithTimeout(ctx: Context, timeoutMilliseconds: number): [Context, function]
    • Defined in index.ts:209

    WithTimeout returns WithDeadline(parent, Date.now() + timeout).

    Canceling this context releases resources associated with it, so code should call cancel as soon as the operations running in this Context complete.

    Parameters

    • ctx: Context

      The parent context

    • timeoutMilliseconds: number

      The number of milliseconds before the deadline will be exceeded

    Returns [Context, function]

WithValue

  • WithValue(ctx: Context, key: string, value: any): [Context, function]
    • Defined in index.ts:275

    WithValue returns a copy of parent in which the value associated with key is val.

    Use context Values only for request-scoped data that transits processes and APIs, not for passing optional parameters to functions.

    Parameters

    • ctx: Context

      The parent context

    • key: string

      The key associated with val in the returned context

    • value: any

    Returns [Context, function]
